sentences: Jeffery Wayne Bates (born September 19, 1963) is an American country music artist.
Signed to RCA Nashville in late 2002, Bates released his debut album Rainbow Man in May 2003.

A second album, Leave the Light On, was released in 2005 on RCA.
He left RCA in 2006.
This album was followed by Jeff Bates in 2008 on the independent Black River Entertainment.
Before signing to a record contract, Bates co-wrote Tracy Lawrence's 2002 single "What a Memory".

sentences: He signed to Black River Entertainment in 2008 and released his self-titled third album.
In January 2009 he released his first Christmas single "That's What Christmas Is" with Jimmy Fortune of The Statler Brothers fame singing background vocals.
Jeff's second and first EP for Black River, "One Day Closer" was released February 15, 2011.
After signing a contract with Warner-Chappell Publishing, Bates developed a methamphetamine addiction in late 1999.
On March 14, 2001, he was arrested for drug possession and grand theft.
In August 2006, a $3,500 guitar that was a gift to Bates from the Takamine guitar company and used in his video "One Second Chance" was stolen from Bates's garage.
Mavity was the same officer involved in Bates's arrest in 2001.
In May 2007, Bates married his girlfriend, Kelly Vaughn, in an outdoor ceremony.
In January 2009 he released his first Christmas single "That's What Christmas Is" with Jimmy Fortune of The Statler Brothers fame singing background vocals.
One Day Closer =
Jeff's second and first EP for Black River, "One Day Closer" was released February 15, 2011.
A year later, he signed to Black River Music Group and released his self-titled third album.
